Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.02,0:00:04.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The rhythm of the wind brightens deductions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.00,0:00:06.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We can even see the bonds of black come undone!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.08,0:00:08.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow, this reeks of the men in black.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.06,0:00:10.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, we'll figure out the motive of the case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.28,0:00:11.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.90,0:00:14.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.04,0:00:16.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.04,0:00:16.20,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.45,0:01:45.39,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Excuse me! Detective Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.39,0:01:47.08,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}About this murder case...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.73,0:01:49.13,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}When Mr. Nagumo was arrested,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.13,0:01:55.34,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}he said he killed Kazami-san because he couldn't take seeing him attack his son, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.34,0:01:58.60,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His motive is none of my business.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.58,0:02:02.44,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}All I did was reveal the trick he used,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.44,0:02:07.49,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and advise him to turn himself in while he had the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.49,0:02:08.67,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.67,0:02:10.40,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ah, Mouri-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.40,0:02:12.63,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Tell us more!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.80,0:02:18.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Turning my back to the press...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.64,0:02:21.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I look so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.38,0:02:24.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.66,0:02:28.61,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now that he's actually solved a case himself, there's no tearing him away from the TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.27,0:02:32.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Well, I {\i1}did{\i0} make the old guy into a great detective
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.14,0:02:35.76,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}to get the attention of the men in black and learn more about them,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.76,0:02:37.87,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}but so far, the plan's been a bust.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.87,0:02:39.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's watch that tape one more time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.35,0:02:43.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}They collect large sums of cash by repeating assassinations,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.30,0:02:46.99,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}they force people like Haibara to make strange drugs,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.99,0:02:50.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and go around gathering competent computer programmers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.77,0:02:56.86,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But... But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.23,0:03:02.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, this is the Mouri Detective Agency...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.49,0:03:06.91,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I doubt they're planning to spend all that money to release a cool new video game...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.36,0:03:08.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? A video game?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.06,0:03:14.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A software engineer is missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.20,0:03:18.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... yes... and you want us to find him...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.13,0:03:20.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Tell 'em I'm out!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.35,0:03:25.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've gotta retape today's rerun of Yoko-chan's TV drama so I can cut out the commercials!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.93,0:03:29.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, come down to the office right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.32,0:03:31.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad seems to be free!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.92,0:03:35.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, straighten your tie and shave!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.81,0:03:37.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.69,0:03:40.38,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A video game programmer is missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.56,0:03:42.44,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.70,0:03:44.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.85,0:04:02.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is Itakura-san, the programmer who went missing a week ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.52,0:04:08.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said this isn't the first time you've lost him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.87,0:04:10.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.03,0:04:15.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He often disappears when we're close to a big deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.50,0:04:18.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we thought the same this time too,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.42,0:04:22.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but we can't sit around waiting for him to resurface any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.79,0:04:26.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The last time this happened we called the police, and he threw a fit over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.40,0:04:29.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We thought you could be more discreet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:33.25,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}They don't seem to have anything to do with the guys I'm looking for...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.83,0:04:37.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you manage to track him down, please call me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.46,0:04:41.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you gotta be kidding! My place is dishing out the most cash!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.36,0:04:46.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Our company is the one who ordered a program from him first!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.60,0:04:51.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er, you don't all work for the same company?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.04,0:04:56.37,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Katsumichi Sugai (39)\NGo Game Development Company Executive
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.62,0:05:00.38,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Johei Naito (47)\NChess Game Development Company Executive
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.67,0:05:04.76,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryusuke Soma (44)\NShogi Game Development Company Executive
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.98,0:04:56.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My company asked Itakura to create a virtual Go game. My name's Sugai.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.94,0:05:00.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Naito. He's developing a chess game for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.03,0:05:04.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We hired him to create a Shogi game. The name's Soma.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.49,0:05:09.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Three computerized board games at once?\NCan one programmer do all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.71,0:05:12.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we want to find him!\NTo confront him about lying to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.69,0:05:19.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When we each hired him, he told us this:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.07,0:05:23.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I haven't signed any contracts with anyone right now, so leave it to me."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.69,0:05:26.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How'd you find out he was trying to do three jobs at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.02,0:05:31.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A week ago, we all got this e-mail from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.26,0:05:35.37,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It hasn't been easy doing three jobs at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.00,0:05:38.75,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But lately my heart's been pretty strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.75,0:05:42.00,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I think I'll work away from my office for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.00,0:05:44.02,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Keep your hats on, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.64,0:05:44.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I know him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.74,0:05:47.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't recognize him in the photo because he was wearing glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.94,0:05:51.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that Suguru Itakura-san, the famous CGI designer?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.19,0:05:52.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.67,0:05:55.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He wears contacts in public.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.64,0:05:56.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.03,0:06:00.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His name's in the credits of all the big movies!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.53,0:06:03.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Three years ago his eyesight started to deteriorate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.95,0:06:08.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So he changed his focus to computer programming and video game graphics.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.46,0:06:13.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If he's a big shot, maybe he's been kidnapped?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.97,0:06:15.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Get real!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.19,0:06:18.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.69,0:06:23.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A couple of years ago, I saw a suspicious character hanging around Itakura's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.69,0:06:27.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a big man with a mustache and a Kansai accent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.16,0:06:31.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys must've seen him too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.54,0:06:35.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was at the big Mantendo ceremony a while back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.82,0:06:38.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}T-Tequila!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.04,0:06:42.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, why was the big man there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.31,0:06:45.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What were they talking about at the office?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.14,0:06:48.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Beats me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.07,0:06:53.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was there, all I heard him say was, "I've got no use for you anymore!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.02,0:06:56.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all? Isn't there more?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.03,0:06:58.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-kun, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.02,0:07:03.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Damn! I've got to find this Itakura-san and ask him myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.93,0:07:09.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know the guy you're talking about, he died in an explosion. So he couldn't be involved in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.56,0:07:13.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now how can I find this person with just a photo to go on?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.52,0:07:16.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it was taken in a hotel room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.92,0:07:21.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We called some local hotels, but they were all very protective of their guests' privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.71,0:07:24.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably checked in under a false name anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.75,0:07:27.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ran-neechan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.59,0:07:32.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we have sashimi, tenshinhan and beef stew for dinner tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.02,0:07:34.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That's Japanese, Chinese and western-style food!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.37,0:07:38.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even a big family restaurant will have all that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.19,0:07:40.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, if I ordered all that stuff at once,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.73,0:07:43.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the waiters would think I was pretty weird, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.54,0:07:44.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.77,0:07:51.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, this guy's got a Shogi board, a Go board, and a chess board in his room...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.70,0:07:56.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know if he took anything out of his office when he left?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.51,0:08:01.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One of his employees told me he took his laptop and a few computer disks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.01,0:08:05.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And he didn't take anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.27,0:08:05.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.63,0:08:09.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is wrong with this hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.94,0:08:11.71,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm sorry, who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.71,0:08:15.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the guest who borrowed a set of Shogi, chess and Go boards!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.61,0:08:18.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The phone in my room isn't working!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.42,0:08:21.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm calling from my cell phone, and I expect you to fix this problem immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.76,0:08:25.97,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We don't loan out any board games to guests at this hotel...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.97,0:08:28.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oops, sorry, wrong number!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.17,0:08:32.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, next up is Hotel New Beika...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.48,0:08:37.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No one else would order a bunch of board games from the front desk
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.52,0:08:39.90,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and hang onto them for a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.71,0:08:44.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A strange guest like that would be the talk of the hotel staff!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.18,0:08:47.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm calling from my cell phone, and I expect you to fix this problem—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.99,0:08:50.66,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ah, yes. Itakura-sama in room 2004, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.38,0:08:53.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right, room 2004.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.68,0:08:57.25,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'll send someone up to your room right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.25,0:09:01.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Huh? It looks like the phone was just unplugged.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.38,0:09:03.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.97,0:09:07.63,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hotel New Beika, room 2004!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.67,0:09:12.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez! Why are you two coming along?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.84,0:09:14.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll just get in the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.68,0:09:16.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Conan-kun wanted to come...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.55,0:09:18.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No fair, Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.25,0:09:19.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After you get paid for solving the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.15,0:09:22.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you're gonna have a fancy meal at the hotel restaurant, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.95,0:09:25.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.52,0:09:28.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we find Itakura-san, we'll treat you all to dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.95,0:09:31.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.95,0:09:38.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is his hideout, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.96,0:09:42.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One thing's been bugging me. Aren't you all business rivals?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.66,0:09:45.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you come to me as a group?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.01,0:09:50.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found out from that e-mail that he took jobs from all three of us at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.49,0:09:54.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The three of us project leaders decided to talk to him together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.13,0:09:57.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I came up with the idea of hiring you, Mouri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.98,0:10:01.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it was {\i1}me{\i0}! {\i1}I{\i0} said we should hire a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.88,0:10:04.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm the one who suggested Mouri-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.96,0:10:08.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Step off, both of you! I'm the one who called his office!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.12,0:10:11.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, I was the one who came up with the idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.23,0:10:11.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.68,0:10:15.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Aw, Yoko-chan's TV drama's already over...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.44,0:10:20.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My, wearing a cheap watch like that's sure to get some snide remarks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.38,0:10:23.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Itakura-san's not going to like that cheap watch of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.88,0:10:24.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why...see?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.94,0:10:26.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of us too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.00,0:10:28.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way is that real!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:31.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To hell with you! It's brand-new, I just bought it five days ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.49,0:10:34.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think {\i1}yours{\i0} is a knockoff!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.84,0:10:46.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Naito-san, would you press the button for the 20th floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.15,0:10:47.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.54,0:10:49.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.09,0:10:58.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Itakura-san's going to be so surprised when he sees everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.27,0:10:59.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.51,0:11:04.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But is it okay to head for the hotel room just like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.34,0:11:08.59,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Itakura-san is someone who is involved somehow with Tequila, a member of the Organization...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.02,0:11:14.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I wonder if it's safe for Ran, the old guy, and these people to go to his room...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.61,0:11:20.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Those last words that Tequila said to Itakura-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.24,0:11:22.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"I've got no use for you anymore!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:25.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Does that mean the Organization's trying to kill him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.47,0:11:28.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What if those guys are hiding nearby
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.56,0:11:30.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}in order to get rid of Itakura-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.29,0:11:34.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Or maybe they're already in his room?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.44,0:11:40.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Nah, you're just getting paranoid. Get a hold of yourself...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.85,0:11:43.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Tequila said that two years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.72,0:11:48.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If the men in black had wanted to kill Itakura-san, he'd be long dead by now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.94,0:11:52.22,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And if Itakura-san were one of the men in black,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.22,0:11:54.09,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}he wouldn't have let Soma-san into his office
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.09,0:11:57.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}while he was talking with Tequila.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.19,0:12:03.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Anyway, I'll just have to meet Itakura-san
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.18,0:12:05.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and try to get him to talk about that meeting with Tequila.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.60,0:12:11.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I've got to find out why Tequila came to his office...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.32,0:12:24.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd. He's got a "do not disturb" sign hanging on the door, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.65,0:12:27.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've gone out for a bite to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.08,0:12:29.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We can wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.89,0:12:33.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.07,0:12:38.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The door locks automatically, so please remember to carry your room key!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.67,0:12:39.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.82,0:12:43.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.06,0:12:48.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you open my uncle's room too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.65,0:12:53.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he forgot we were coming to see him, and went somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.87,0:12:54.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.93,0:12:57.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! I gotta go potty!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.78,0:12:59.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.20,0:13:02.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I gotta go, I gotta go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.78,0:13:04.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Er... Thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.14,0:13:10.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Smart work, little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.99,0:13:17.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If Itakura-san comes back and sees us out in the hall, he might try to run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.86,0:13:21.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay, kid. Looks like we won't need to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.18,0:13:25.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Itakura-san's napping at his desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.73,0:13:27.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.98,0:13:30.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wake up! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.66,0:13:34.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't escape us now, Itakura-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.57,0:13:41.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.07,0:13:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\q2\a10\c&H9FFFFF&\4c&H000000&\bord0\shad1\alpha&HFF&\b0\fs26\fscx186\fscy200}Original Broadcast Date:\NJanuary 27, 2003\N{\fs13} \N{\fs26}Based on manga:\NVol. 37 Files 5-8
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.93,0:13:52.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Itakura-san! Itakura-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.98,0:13:57.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Save your breath. He's been dead for over a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.31,0:13:59.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.99,0:14:01.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.33,0:14:04.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How could this have happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.90,0:14:07.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.52,0:14:09.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There are pills scattered all over the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.52,0:14:12.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was struck by a sudden attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.75,0:14:16.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and reached for his medication, but he couldn't take it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.10,0:14:21.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez. That's what he gets for cutting himself off from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.24,0:14:26.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.95,0:14:30.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Itakura-san didn't die of an illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.01,0:14:31.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Somebody killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.05,0:14:33.94,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But...why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.94,0:14:38.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why do I keep losing them just when I think I'm on their trail?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.23,0:14:42.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.81,0:14:45.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.83,0:14:46.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A diary?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.76,0:14:51.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Itakura-san's diary...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.48,0:14:56.08,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If so, maybe there's something in it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.84,0:14:59.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It could tell me why Tequila came to see Itakura-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.20,0:15:06.67,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and what the men in black are trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.67,0:15:10.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'll find the answers to everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.16,0:15:11.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.44,0:15:15.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare touch the possessions of the deceased!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.72,0:15:19.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, I can't take my eyes off you for a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.47,0:15:22.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Damn! I can't do a thing about it after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.93,0:15:27.51,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If I want to read that diary, I'll have to make him understand
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.51,0:15:31.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}that Itakura-san didn't die of natural causes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.54,0:15:33.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That heart attack was faked.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.66,0:15:40.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And there's a good chance it was one of those three people!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.95,0:15:47.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased is Suguru Itakura-san, age 45,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.09,0:15:50.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,a video game programmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.26,0:15:53.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the cause of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.71,0:15:58.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to do a detailed analysis to know for sure, but I don't see any external injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.11,0:16:02.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from the fact that he took coronary dilators,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.02,0:16:04.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm guessing he was overcome by a sudden heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.98,0:16:07.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I estimate he's been dead for at least two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.74,0:16:10.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! I've contacted Itakura-san's doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.65,0:16:12.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.76,0:16:16.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Itakura had a very weak heart. He had to take medication three times a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.08,0:16:20.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was scheduled for a coronary operation once he'd finished his projects.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.94,0:16:22.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That would mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.52,0:16:25.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess we won't need {\i1}you{\i0} this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.40,0:16:27.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.46,0:16:34.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if he's been dead for two days, why didn't the hotel staff notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.72,0:16:38.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He hated having people in his workspace.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.33,0:16:40.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.63,0:16:45.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Once he flipped out at me because he thought the papers on his desk had moved 10 cm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.34,0:16:49.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And he rarely changes his sheets at home either,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.08,0:16:51.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he probably refused to have his bed made for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.88,0:16:54.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are those three guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.35,0:16:58.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Executives from game companies Itakura-san worked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.96,0:17:05.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They hired me to look for Itakura-san because he'd been missing for a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.41,0:17:10.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you found him, but he was already dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.55,0:17:12.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.36,0:17:15.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he locked himself away in a dirty, unhealthy environment
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.52,0:17:17.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,even though he knew he had a bad heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.52,0:17:19.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He brought it on himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.73,0:17:20.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.51,0:17:24.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he liked to keep things really clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.28,0:17:31.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When we came into the room, he was face down at the desk,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.97,0:17:34.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but the desktop was dry! No drool marks!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.92,0:17:38.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Drool?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.25,0:17:40.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at all the drool on his face!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.38,0:17:42.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone drools as much as he did,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.20,0:17:44.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it would usually dirty the desk too, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.65,0:17:46.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've wiped the desk clean!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.83,0:17:53.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dumb kid! Why would a guy in the throes of a heart attack stop to clean off his desk?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.16,0:17:55.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who cleaned it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.16,0:17:58.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.59,0:18:03.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, you didn't tell me you found him face down at the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.52,0:18:06.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he fell when I shook him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.24,0:18:08.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true, there's something funny here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.46,0:18:11.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The corpse's hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.30,0:18:16.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His hands are locked tightly against his chest due to rigor mortis.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.80,0:18:20.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They should have been pressed against the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.14,0:18:23.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't see any pressure marks on his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.75,0:18:28.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe Itakura-san died somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.04,0:18:34.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Inspector, his hands and legs are completely rigid in this position!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.31,0:18:41.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, unless someone tied Itakura-san to the chair, he couldn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.52,0:18:46.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.54,0:18:52.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Itakura-san was tied to the chair with his hands against his chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.23,0:18:55.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he couldn't reach his medicine in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.49,0:18:58.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you think this is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.73,0:19:00.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.14,0:19:02.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something we know all too well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.21,0:19:05.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.75,0:19:07.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.72,0:19:13.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if that's true, there ought to be rope marks on the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.60,0:19:15.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, coroner?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.60,0:19:18.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any clear markings,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.41,0:19:22.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but there are faint blood stasis marks around his shoulders and knees,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.50,0:19:24.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as if his body had been constricted there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.74,0:19:26.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.87,0:19:30.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh, this blanket is so soft and warm!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.86,0:19:33.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.39,0:19:37.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what's this? It's kinda sticky in places.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.36,0:19:41.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I've got it! The blanket!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.85,0:19:43.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Blanket?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.20,0:19:48.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder wrapped Itakura-san's body in the blanket, sat him in the chair,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.57,0:19:52.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then held him in place with duct tape or something similar!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.27,0:19:55.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A pillow or something was placed between his chest and knees
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.38,0:19:58.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so his body would take the shape of the desk!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.65,0:20:01.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! That wouldn't leave any rope marks on the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.43,0:20:07.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To make it work, the chair would have had to have been fixed to the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.21,0:20:13.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to have been wiped off, but I can see traces of duct tape adhesive on the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.11,0:20:22.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer left Itakura-san there as he was until he died of a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.02,0:20:24.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then after rigor mortis had set in,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.64,0:20:27.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer returned, removed the duct tape and blanket,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.76,0:20:30.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and turned his body against the desk to make the death look natural!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.01,0:20:33.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, question the hotel staff!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.13,0:20:37.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask them if any suspicious-looking people have visited in the last two or three days!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.40,0:20:38.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.73,0:20:40.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The hotel...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.87,0:20:41.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.93,0:20:46.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found this room by calling the hotel and pretending to be Itakura-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.72,0:20:52.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I told them I was the one who'd borrowed Shogi, chess and Go sets from the front desk,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.26,0:20:54.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the phone in my room wasn't working.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.10,0:20:59.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I got the number of this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.86,0:21:04.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, the clerk on the other end started laughing, and said, "Again?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.09,0:21:11.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? You mean to say that someone else used the same trick to to find this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.76,0:21:16.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it would take a brilliant deductive mind to rival my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.26,0:21:18.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.20,0:21:19.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A few days ago, someone claiming to be Itakura-san
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.46,0:21:23.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,called the hotel desk and said the phone in his room wasn't working!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.11,0:21:24.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.95,0:21:30.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When a clerk went to Itakura-san's room, he shooed her away, saying, "It wasn't me!"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.52,0:21:35.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's safe to say that was the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.72,0:21:42.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So how did you know Itakura-san had borrowed Shogi, chess and Go boards from the hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.24,0:21:43.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.43,0:21:49.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw a video e-mail that Itakura-san sent those three.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.55,0:21:55.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And in it, Itakura-san had a Shogi board, a chess board and a Go board in front of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.37,0:21:58.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.39,0:22:06.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Any one of you could've used the same method as Mouri-kun to find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.96,0:22:10.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.71,0:22:12.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:19.86,Signs,Typesetting,0,0,0,,Ashita wo Yumemite\N"Dreaming of Tomorrow"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.36,0:22:29.76,Detective Conan - end song eng,,0000,0000,0000,,When I hear your voice come from over the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.76,0:22:35.29,Detective Conan - end song eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I'm strong, I feel like I want to cry
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.33,0:22:42.59,Detective Conan - end song eng,,0000,0000,0000,,We hurt each other, but I still want to see you again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.75,0:22:48.34,Detective Conan - end song eng,,0000,0000,0000,,We always parted without being able to face each other
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.63,0:22:55.97,Detective Conan - end song eng,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wondering how to reply, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.52,0:23:04.11,Detective Conan - end song eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever I remember that expression you could never hide
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.20,0:23:21.92,Detective Conan - end song eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Dreaming of tomorrow... I want to believe you, though it's hard to do
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.21,0:23:30.55,Detective Conan - end song eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Dreaming of tomorrow... I want to see you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.72,0:23:39.18,Detective Conan - end song eng,,0000,0000,0000,,I can still faintly see the sun through the leaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.56,0:23:51.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like Itakura-san's been keeping a diary every day for the past five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.02,0:23:55.68,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That means it's there! It's there!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.68,0:23:59.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}From when Tequila came to visit two years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.37,0:24:01.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.47,0:24:02.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.81,0:24:05.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Itakura-san left it over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.17,0:24:11.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A dying message, pointing to the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.11,0:24:17.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan: The Silent Testimony Left Behind (Part 2)!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.12,0:24:27.13,Signs,Typesetting,0,0,0,,Please look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.34,0:24:23.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{コナン「次回は解決！」}Next time, the solution!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.25,0:24:25.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{高木刑事「警部、我々で白黒つけましょう！」}Let's solve this one ourselves, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.06,0:24:26.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{目暮警部「ヨシッ！毛利くんを寝かせるな！」}Alright, don't let Mouri-kun fall asleep!
